<p>I have AngularJS webapp and start it with <strong>Tomcat 7</strong>. Using <code>$locationProvider.html5Mode(true)</code> I remove hash '#' from url</p>  <pre><code>localhost:8080/App/#/login -&gt; localhost:8080/App/login </code></pre>  <p>But now, when I refresh <code>localhost:8080/App/login</code> I have <code>404 error</code>. How to configure Tomcat7 for <code>localhost:8080/App/login</code> refresh?</p>  <p>app.config:</p>  <pre><code>$urlRouterProvider.otherwise("/login/");  $stateProvider         .state('home', {             abstract: true,             templateUrl: 'dist/view/home.html',             controller: 'HomeCtrl'         });  $locationProvider.html5Mode(true); </code></pre>  <p>index.html:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;head&gt;     &lt;meta charset="utf-8"&gt;     &lt;script&gt;         document.write('&lt;base href="' + document.location + '" /&gt;');     &lt;/script&gt; &lt;/head&gt; </code></pre>